author: Jim Kleinpeter, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: Former LSU star La'el Collins now a starter for Dallas Cowboys
text:
Former LSU star offensive lineman La'el Collins has been named the starter at left guard for the Dallas Cowboys, Jon Machota of the Dallas Morning News tweeted. The Cowboys have a bye this week.
Collins will make his second career start against the New York Giants in Week 7 in place of Ronald Leary. He has played in two games and has not allowed a sack or quarterback pressure in 57 snaps. He replaced Leary, who sat out with an injured back, earlier in the season.
Collins was an All-American who played from 2011-14 at LSU and signed with the Cowboys as an undrafted free agent . He was passed over in the NFL draft last April because of a murder investigation in which his former girlfriend and her unborn child were victims. Collins was never a suspect and was ultimately cleared in the investigation .
La'el Collins: "[This is] definitely the start of showing I'm becoming the player I want to be. Just taking that approach every day."
— Jon Machota (@jonmachota) October 14, 2015 La'el Collins is the new starter at left guard
— Jon Machota (@jonmachota) October 14, 2015
